comment: [Observable in enhanced video] LHH shows that Lawson (HOU) moves his pivot foot when he attempts to maintain his position during defensive pressure.
Ariza (HOU) makes body to body contact with Griffin (LAC) as he secures the rebound.
Redick (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Harden (HOU) on the perimeter.
Harden (HOU) clamps Redick (LAC) then shoves him while trying to create separation on the perimeter.
LATR shows Redick (LAC) makes contact with Harden's (HOU) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Thornton (HOU) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Griffin's (LAC) shot attempt.

RATR shows Howard (HOU) makes contact with the ball while part of it is still in the cylinder above the basket ring. As per the Rule Book, goaltending is only reviewable when there is a call on the floor. Since there was no call, the play is not reviewable.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the out of bounds should result in a jump ball was overturned and HOU was awarded possession.
Griffin (LAC) commits a take foul on Lawson (HOU).
